Cook pasta according to package directions; drain. In large skillet over medium-high heat, add 3 tablespoons oil. Add broccoli, bell peppers, onions, zucchini, squash and 1 tablespoon garlic. Salt and pepper to taste. Saute vegetables until tender (about 8 to 10 minutes); remove from skillet and keep warm. Add 3 tablespoons oil, shrimp and remaining garlic to skillet. Salt and pepper to taste. Sear shrimp 3 to 4 minutes per side or until opaque and cooked through. Toss with warm vegetables, pasta, Parmesan cheese and basil.